This paper proposes a method for reducing constituent parsing to sequence labeling, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to achieve high accuracy, which is a common theme in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves encoding nonterminal symbols, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions achieving fast parsing speeds, which is a common theme in the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV).
